sect2.para:
   The basic format of a XPM is an array composed as follows:


/* XPM */
static char * <pixmap name>[] = {
"Values-string",
"Colors-strings",
"Pixel-strings"
};

   Note that the header comment with only the word XPM in it is required.
   I leave out the Extension strings as we don't need them here.

example.programlisting:
/* XPM */
static char * dot[] = {
"5 5 2 1",
". c None",
"X c Red",
"  X  ",
" XXX ",
"XXXXX",
" XXX ",
"  X  ",
};

sect1.para:
As both functions are identical in usage, I will describe pixmap_create_from_xpm_d only.
list( $pixmap, $mask) = gdk::pixmap_create_from_xpm_d( $objWindow->window, $colTransparent, $arImage);
The function returns an array of size 2: the first is the map with all the pixels and colors, and the second is the mask with transparency information. We store them in two different variables here, although you can just use an array.

The second parameter, $colTransparent defines the transparent color of the image, additionally to the defined None colors in the XPM.
$colTransparent = &new GdkColor(0, 0, 0);
It doesn't seem to work with php-gtk, so you have to use the None color in the pixmap definition.
